{"lemma":"خَشِن","slug":"خَشِن","root":"خ.ش.ن","root_slug":"خ-ش-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ش-ن","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n10712","","n10716"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%90%D9%86"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be coarse, to be rude, to be uncouth, to be rough, to be hoarse"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make coarse, to render rough"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"rough (not smooth), hard to the touch; coarse (not fine)","examples":[{"text":"وَٱلشَّكْوَسُ قَالَ أَبُو ٱلْخَيْرِ وَغَيْرِهِ هُوَ ٱلْوَرْدُ ٱلْفَحْصِيُّ وَقِيلَ ٱلْبَرِيُّ وَهُوَ نَوْعَانِ أَحَدُهُمَا يُسَمَّى بِٱلْعَجَمِيَّةِ ٱلرَّحْبَلُ وَرَقُهُ فِي قَدْرِ وَرَقِ ٱلزَّيْتُونِ وَأَطْوَلُ وَأَعْرَضُ أََغْبَرُ أَحْرَشُ وَأَغْصَانُهُ خَشِنَةٌ صُلْبَةٌ إِلَى ٱلْبَيَاضِ مَا هِيَ تَطْلَعُ فِي زَمَنِ ٱلرَّبِيعِ نُوْرُهُ كَٱلْوَرْدِ حَمْرَاءُ فَائِتَةٌ وَفِي وَسَطِهَا صُفْرَةٌ وَهَذَا هُوَ ٱلْمُسَمَّى ٱلْوَرْدُ ٱلْفَحْصِيُّ وَيُقَالُ إِنَّ ٱلْوَرْدَ إِنْ رَكِبَ فِيهِ فَيَنْجِبُ وَٱلنَّوْعُ ٱلثَّانِي مِنَ ٱلشَّكْوَسِ وَرَقُهُ أَصْغَرُ مِنْ وَرَقِ ٱلْأَوَّلِ وَأَشَدُّ خُضْرَةً وَهًوَ أَحْرَشُ بَيْنَ ٱلْاِسْتِدَارِ وَٱلطُّولِ وَأَغْصَانِهِ إِلَى ٱلْحَمْرَاءِ مَا هِيَ تَطْلَعُ وَرْدًا أَبْيَضَا نَاصِعَةً فِي وَسَطِهَا وَكِلَاهُمَا لَاحِقٌ بِٱلْأَشْجَارِ.","english":"And the rockrose, say Abū al-Ḵayr and others, is the field rose, and also the land rose, it is said, and there are two kinds: One is called in Berber raḥbal and its leaves are of the dimensions of the leaves of the olive but longer and wider, more gray and rugged, and its branches are rough, stiff and lean into white, and in spring it blossoms in roses of a red hue you almost miss, and in their mid there is yellow and this is called field rose, and it is said that if a rose is grafted onto it it will prevail. The second kind of rockrose has smaller leaves than the first, of a more intense green, and it is more rugged around and along, and its branches lean into red and spawn white roses, vivid in the middle. And both liaise with trees."}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"rude, uncouth, rough of manners"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"tough (life)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"hoarse, gruff, raspy, gravelly"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/xa.ʃin/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n10712","headword_ar":"خَشُنَ","root":"x$n","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$uwnapN","text_ar":"خُشُونَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$onapN","text_ar":"خُشْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, KL) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$aAnapN","text_ar":"خَشَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(CK, TA, but omitted in some copies of the K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$onN","text_ar":"خَشْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxo$anapN","text_ar":"مَخْشَنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, rough, harsh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * KL, PS;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAna","text_ar":"لَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naEuma","text_ar":"نَعُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tx$~n","text_ar":"تخشّن","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa *uw xa$onapK","text_ar":"هُوَ ذُو خَشْنَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$uwnapK","text_ar":"خُشُونَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxo$anapK","text_ar":"مَخْشَنَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is difficult, refractory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stubborn; not to be coped with."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$inN","text_ar":"خَشِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$una Ealayohi Sadorihi","text_ar":"خَشُنَ عَلَيْهِ صَدْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elyh Sdrh","text_ar":"عليه صدره"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ax$w$n","text_ar":"اخشوشن","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, angry with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, TA.) See also 3."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","KL","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n10716","headword_ar":"خَشِنٌ","root":"x$n","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rough, harsh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, * K, KL, PS;) applied to a thing (S, Msb, K) of any kind; (K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axo$anu","text_ar":"اَخْشَنُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) in relation to a stone, they seldom or never say otherwise than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axo$anu","text_ar":"اَخْشَنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the fem. of the former is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, K;) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$unN","text_ar":"خُشُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) [also said to be a pl. by poetic license of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axo$anu","text_ar":"اَخْشَنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$onN","text_ar":"خُشْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as will be seen below,] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xi$aAnN","text_ar":"خِشَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which is applied in the sense explained above to land [or lands]: (TA:) the fem. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axo$anu","text_ar":"اَخْشَنُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$onaA='u","text_ar":"خَشْنَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu$onN","text_ar":"خُشْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN xa$inapN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ خَشِنَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rugged, ground"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"x$onaA='u","text_ar":"خشْنَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rugged ground"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which are stones and sand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulaA='apN","text_ar":"مُلَا=ءَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$onaA='u","text_ar":"خَشْنَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"[A wrapper for the body] in which is roughness, harshness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarseness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from newness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from make."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] (assumed tropical:)  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong"},{"kind":"text","text":"man. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa xa$inu AljaAnibi","text_ar":"هُوَ خَشِنُ الجَانِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axo$anuhu","text_ar":"اَخْشَنُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is difficult, refractory,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stubborn; not to be coped with."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA. [See also 1.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaA$a Eayo$FA xa$inFA","text_ar":"عَاشَ عَيْشًا خَشِنًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He lived a rough,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse, life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axo$anu","text_ar":"اَخْشَنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","JK"]}]}}